on and take a cookie or a slice of cake. Everything is ruined. You couldn\'t even make it four days, what were you thinking? Well, you might as well just eat 4 cookies, another slice of cake, and 2 ropes of licorice, because you\'ve ruined the diet anyway, what does it matter now?\r\n\r\nThat\'s guilt talking. We\'re all human; we have needs, desires, and momentary lapses in judgement where we make mistakes. The first thing to keep in mind is that feeling guilty about a mistake can lead to very destructive behavior. You ate a cookie. So what? It was good, enjoy it. Now, you\'ve had your fun and it\'s time to recommit to that healthy eating lifestyle. Maybe you had set a goal to fix that bug last night, but instead you binge watched Stranger Things 2 until 1 AM. It\'s okay. Forgive yourself, then recommit and set a new goal in the morning.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNo matter what your approach to getting motivated, the most important piece is always to stay focused on the goal. Whether big or small, it feels great to accomplish the goals we set for ourselves and make our lives better in the process. Take the time to write down a few goals that you would like to accomplish this week, month, or year, and really focus on accomplishing them. You\'ll feel great about yourself, raise your confidence, and improve your life in the process. Happy motivating!","7 Ways to get Motivated and Accomplish your Goals","","inherit","closed","closed","","97-revision-v1","","","2017-11-02 20:25:06","2017-11-02 20:25:06","",97,"http://evingrost.dev/97-revision-v1/",0,"revision","",0),
